The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for non-Euclidean geometric data, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The examples given in the abstract also suggest that computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) may be relevant fields of study. Additionally, the mention of sensor networks (cs.SI) and brain imaging (cs.NE) suggest that these sub-categories may also be relevant.
